<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-3-5-2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title>First Example of Proof by Contraposition</title>

    <p><alert>Prove:</alert> <m>\forall m \in \mathbb{Z} </m> if <m>m^2</m> is odd, then <m>m</m> is odd.</p>

    <p>Before we begin any proof we sing our song (play-along):</p>
        <p>"What's the <m>{\color{red}{P}}</m>?"</p> 
        <answer>
        <p><m>m^2</m> is odd</p>
        </answer>
        <p>"What's the <m>{\color{blue}{Q}}</m>?"</p> 
        <answer>
        <p><m>m</m> is odd</p>
        </answer>
        <p>"What're the definitions?" </p>
        <answer>
        <p>Odd and even! (found in <xref ref="subsec-4-1-2-terms"/>)</p>
        </answer>
        <p>"Now, what to do?"</p> 
        <answer>
        <p>Proof by contraposition - because I said so this time</p>
        </answer>

    <p><alert>The Breakdown:</alert></p>
    <p>
        <me>
            {\color{orange}{\forall m\in\Z}}\text{ if }{\color{red}{m^2 \text{ is odd }}}\text{ then }
            {\color{blue}{m\text{ is odd}}}
        </me>
        
    </p>


<section xml:id="sec-3-5-2-example-begin" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title><m>{\color{red}{\text{The Beginning}}}</m></title>
    <p>Just like before, "shovel off" the invisible quantifier and assume the <m>{\color{red}{P}}</m>.</p>
    <p>Let <m>m</m> be an integer. Assume <m>m</m> is even.</p>
</section>

<section xml:id="sec-3-5-2-example-muddle" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title><m>{\color{green}{\text{The Muddle}}}</m></title>
    <p>Thus by definition of even we can find an integer <m>k</m> such that <m>m=2k</m></p>
    <p>Calculate:</p>
    <md>
        <mrow>m^2\amp=(2k)(2k)</mrow>
        <mrow>\amp=2(2k^2)</mrow>
    </md>
</section>

<section xml:id="sec-3-5-2-example-end" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title><m>{\color{blue}{\text{The End}}}</m></title>
    <p>Since <m>2k^2</m> is an integer, according to the definition of even, <m>m^2</m> is even.</p>
    <p>Don't forget to include a wrap up sentence!</p>
    <p>Hence, by proof by contraposition if <m>m^2</m> is odd then m is odd. <m>\square</m></p>

    <p>Now let's see everything written together in a single spot.</p>
<example>

    <p><alert>Prove:</alert> For any integer <m>m</m>, if <m>m^2</m> is odd, then <m>m</m> is odd.</p>
    <p>Let <m>m</m> be an integer. Assume <m>m</m> is even.</p>
    <p>Calculate:</p>
    <md>
        <mrow>m^2\amp=(2k)(2k)</mrow>
        <mrow>\amp=2(2k^2)</mrow>
    </md>
    <p>Since <m>2k^2</m> is an integer, according to the definition of even, <m>m^2</m> is even.</p>
    <p>Hence, by proof by contraposition if <m>m^2</m> is odd then m is odd. <m>\square</m></p>
</example>

</section>

</section>
